title: Power Move: CLICK TO CALL Your Legislator to Protect SNAP, WIC, and Head Start. TAKE ACTION NOW
description:
# Power Move: CLICK TO CALL Your Legislator to Protect SNAP, WIC, and Head Start. TAKE ACTION NOW.

## 📞 Congress is preparing budget cuts that threaten our communities. Use your power. Call now.

Proposed cuts to **SNAP**, **WIC**, and **Head Start** would devastate families—gutting food programs, maternal healthcare, and early childhood education.

These are survival programs. If we don’t act now, millions will lose access to care, nourishment, and the support they need to thrive.

This is your moment to use your voice—and your power.

---

## ✔ What’s at Stake

- **SNAP** helps feed **38+ million people** every month  
  ➤ [USDA SNAP Overview](https://www.fns.usda.gov/snap/supplemental-nutrition-assistance-program)

- **WIC** provides nutrition and health care for **6.6 million women, infants, and children**  
  ➤ [USDA WIC Program](https://www.fns.usda.gov/wic)

- **Head Start** supports **over 1 million children** through meals, mental health, and early learning  
  ➤ [Head Start Facts](https://eclkc.ohs.acf.hhs.gov/about-us/article/head-start-program-facts)

---

## 📣 How to Take Action

✅ **Step 1: Call your Representative and both U.S. Senators**

You have **three federal lawmakers**—your House Representative and two Senators. Call all three.

Need to find them?

- 🏛️ [Look up your Representative (House)](https://www.house.gov/representatives/find-your-representative)  
- 🏛️ [Look up your Senators (Senate)](https://www.senate.gov/senators/senators-contact.htm)

✅ **Step 2: Review the script below** or write your own message

✅ **Step 3: Click the button on this page** to be auto-connected to their office  
(No phone number needed—we’ll dial for you.)

---

## ☎️ Sample Call Script

> Hi, my name is \_\_\_\_ and I’m a constituent from \_\_\_\_ (ZIP code).  
>
> I’m calling to urge you to **fully fund SNAP, WIC, and Head Start** in the federal budget.  
>
> - SNAP helps feed **38+ million people** each month  
> - WIC supports **6.6 million mothers and children** with nutrition and care  
> - Head Start provides early learning and support to **1+ million children**  
>
> These programs helped me [insert your personal story, or why this matters to your family, church, or community].  
>
> Please protect these programs. I’ll be calling each week until I know they’re fully funded.  
>
> Thank you.

---

## 🧭 What Happens When You Call

You’ll first reach a **real operator at the U.S. Capitol Switchboard**.

- Say: “Connect me to [Senator or Representative NAME]”  
- They’ll transfer you directly to their D.C. office  
- If the line is busy or you get voicemail, **leave a message**—it still gets logged

Have your **ZIP code and story ready**—and don’t be afraid to speak from the heart.

---

## 🔁 Keep the Pressure On

✔ Call every week until the vote is done  
✔ Ask 3 friends to call too  
✔ Flood their phone lines—they can’t ignore us

Justice has a League. And you have the power to act.

description:
For May 11 protest:

Meet in the public lot behind the Flanders Professional Building. It’s in the middle of the block bordered by NW 22nd and 23rd, and NW Everett and Flanders.

Please back into a spot by 1:45 so you’re positioned to pull into the caravan when we leave at 2:00.

You are invited to join this additional protest put on by PDX Contra las Deportaciones to protest and remember the victims of the Trump administration’s cruel abductions and deportations.



This a local Indivisible event!

PDX Car Caravan Protest 1.0 was active weekly or more for over a year, 2020-21, and protested racial injustice and police brutality. We are back in version 2.0 as a raucous motorized protest for people who love justice and hate injustice of all varieties. If you are outraged and need to protest but for whatever reason don’t (always)do crowds, standing and marching, roll with us. Keep your foot on the gas. 

More details on bluesky and Facebook: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0

Just as trees root deeply before they rise, we too must ground ourselves to grow. Through gentle yoga and aromatic oils, we’ll tune into the wisdom of nature and the power of collective healing. With each breath, we invite balance; with each movement, we create space to rise.

About LA Compost's Grounded Wellness Program:
LA Compost's Grounded Wellness Workshop Series provides free, hands-on workshops at Community Compost Hubs in Los Angeles, focusing on wellness through soil health, personal well-being, and community connection. Each workshop celebrates the gifts of the earth while fostering meaningful connections with nature and neighbors. Interactive experiences led by local instructors highlight the connections between healthy soil, a thriving planet, and our well-being.

For more info, visit lacompost.org/groundedwellness.

title: Town Hall: Raise the Wage / Reunión pública para aumentar el sueldo mínimo
description:
~ Español Abajo ~

**Raise the minimum wage! A living wage is a moral wage!**

Join us for a town hall event on raising the minimum wage in Rhode Island.

**Do you make less than $20 an hour? Do you, your loved ones, and neighbors struggle to keep up with the rising cost of living?**

Let's do something about it!

A recent Rhode Island Standard of Need report shows that even a full-time job at the current minimum wage isn't enough to afford basic necessities like rent, childcare, food, and transportation. That’s why we’re calling on all Rhode Islanders to join us in urging our state representatives and senators to raise the minimum wage to $20 an hour over the next five years.

Everyone deserves fair pay for a hard day’s work. Raising the wage means more dignity for workers, stronger families, and a healthier local economy. The Rhode Island AFL-CIO stands in strong support of this campaign—and your voice can help make it happen.

~

¡Aumenten el sueldo mínimo! ¡Un sueldo digno es un sueldo justo!

Acompáñennos en un evento comunitario sobre el aumento del sueldo mínimo en Rhode Island.

¿Gana menos de $20 por hora? ¿Usted, sus seres queridos y sus vecinos tienen dificultades para hacer frente al aumento del costo de vida?

Un informe reciente sobre el Estándar de Necesidad de Rhode Island muestra que incluso un trabajo de tiempo completo con el sueldo mínimo no es suficiente para cubrir necesidades básicas como el alquiler, el cuidado infantil, la alimentación y el transporte. Por eso, llamamos a todos los habitantes de Rhode Island para que insten a nuestros representantes estatales y senadores a aumentar el sueldo mínimo a $20 por hora en los próximos cinco años.

Todos merecen un sueldo justo por un día de trabajo duro. Aumentar el sueldo significa más dignidad para los trabajadores, familias más fuertes y una mejor economía local. La AFL-CIO de Rhode Island apoya firmemente esta campaña, y su voz puede ayudar a lograrlo.
